# Maintainer: Genesi OS Team <dev@genesios.org>

pkgname=genesi-ai-mode
pkgver=1.0.0
# 2026-06-07 (53): Turbo fixes for weak/CPU hardware + working speculative
# decoding. (1) CPU-only machines no longer keep the speculative draft model â€”
# a second model on the same cores made Turbo SLOWER than stock on an 8GB
# CPU-only laptop. (2) On GPU, the draft is now offloaded with -ngld 999 so it
# runs on the GPU instead of the CPU (the reason spec decoding "never worked").
# (3) CPU path uses f16 KV + auto flash-attn (q8_0 KV + forced FA only help on
# GPU) and pins threads to the fast/perf cores (skips Intel hybrid E-cores).
# 2026-06-07 (54): (1) Monitor chat now hits llama-server /v1/chat/completions
# (applies the model's chat template + stop tokens) instead of /completion with
# a raw prompt â€” fixes the AI rambling infinite garbage in Turbo. (2) Turbo
# queries nvidia-smi for VRAM when the daemon's state.json has none, so it
# actually offloads to the GPU instead of silently running on CPU. (3) genesi-aid
# re-detects the GPU every ~30s (it was profiled once at boot, before the NVIDIA
# driver was ready) + DRM fallback â€” fixes the dashboard showing "no GPU".
# 2026-06-07 (55): vendor-agnostic VRAM detection. nvidia-smi doesn't work under
# nouveau/NVK (the live ISO driver), so VRAM read as 0 â†’ Turbo thought the model
# "spilled VRAM", dropped the draft and ran on CPU, and the dashboard said "no
# GPU" â€” all on a machine whose 3050 llama.cpp clearly sees via Vulkan. Now both
# genesi-aid and genesi-ai-turbo size the GPU via `llama-server --list-devices`
# (the same Vulkan backend used for inference) when nvidia-smi/sysfs can't, so
# spec decoding actually engages on the GPU and the advisor reports the card.
# 2026-06-07 (56): version-proof Turbo flags + CPU speculative decoding. Recent
# llama.cpp removed --draft (now --spec-draft-n-max), so the draft would crash
# the server the moment spec decoding engaged on the GPU; we now read the
# installed binary's --help and pick the flag it actually supports. Also enable
# model-free n-gram speculative decoding (--spec-type ngram-simple) on CPU-only
# machines (no draft model, no extra RAM) so GPU-less laptops get a speculative
# speedup too. Disable with GENESI_TURBO_NO_NGRAM=1.
# 2026-06-07 (57): actually ENGAGE speculative decoding. Recent llama.cpp loads
# the draft model from -md but does nothing unless --spec-type selects an
# implementation (defaults to 'none' -> "no implementations specified for
# speculative decoding"), so the draft burned VRAM with zero speedup. Now we add
# --spec-type draft-simple whenever a draft is used (when the binary supports it).
# 2026-06-07 (58): VRAM-aware offload (Tier 0). Instead of a blind -ngl 999 that
# OOMs a small/partially-full card, use -ngl auto (fit as many layers as the VRAM
# holds) when the model doesn't fully fit; keep 999 when it fits entirely.
# 2026-06-07 (59): FIX REGRESSION â€” `serve` defaulted to speculative decoding,
# which REGRESSED real-world speed on Vulkan/NVK (plain GPU offload was 21 t/s,
# spec dropped it to ~baseline: the draft + verification cost more than it saves
# without a mature CUDA driver). Default `serve` is back to plain full GPU
# offload (the proven win); speculative decoding is now opt-in (GENESI_TURBO_SPEC
# =1 or an explicit draft). `bench` still compares both so spec can be evaluated.
# 2026-06-07 (60): Lote B â€” named intensity profiles (2.9). New
# `genesi-ai-mode profile max|balanced|battery|auto` + /run profile file the
# daemon reads live (re-applies on change) + segmented control in the Monitor.
# max=full(governor+EPP+power+GPU), balanced=governor+mem+hogs only,
# battery=hogs+mem (governor untouched), auto=AC->max/battery->battery.
# 2026-06-07 (61): Turbo speculative decoding is now a USER CHOICE (still off by
# default). `genesi-ai-turbo --spec/--speculative` flag, and a "offload total â‡„
# âšˇ speculative" toggle on the Monitor's Turbo card (setTurbo carries the spec
# flag â†’ serve --spec). So users can run Turbo with or without speculation.
# 2026-06-07 (62): 2.8.4 â€” pin AI processes to the performance cores. On hybrid
# Intel CPUs (P/E) genesi-aid sets the AI process CPU affinity to the P-cores
# (+ HT siblings) so inference never lands on the slow E-cores; restored on
# disable. No-op on uniform CPUs and VMs.
# 2026-06-08 (63): 2.9 â€” benchmark button in the Monitor. The Painel now has a
# "Benchmark de desempenho" card that wraps `genesi-ai-mode bench [model]`: it
# streams each step live (warming up / OFF / ON), then draws an OFF-vs-ON
# tokens/s bar graph with the % gain. Backend (genesi_ai_monitor.py) runs the
# CLI in a worker thread and parses its output (single source of truth stays the
# CLI; no re-implemented measurement). Uses the active/Turbo/first-installed
# model. Note: on a VM the governor is a no-op so expect ~0% â€” the card says so.
# 2026-06-08 (64): Tier 1 â€” predictive preload at login/idle (formalize
# maybe_warm_idle). genesi-aid now persists an MRU of the model weight files the
# user actually loaded to /var/lib/genesi-ai-mode/warm.json (new service
# StateDirectory=genesi-ai-mode, survives reboot). On a fresh boot, while idle,
# the daemon seeds _warm_files from that MRU and warms the LAST-USED model into
# the page cache â€” so the FIRST prompt after login loads from RAM, not disk
# (previously it only warmed the model after you'd already run it once that
# session). Same conservative gates: throttled, skipped on RAM-backed fs, <50%
# of available RAM (no-op on tight 6 GB VMs). Pure reclaimable cache; nothing to
# restore. Best-effort writes never raise into the main loop.
# 2026-06-08 (65): Lote C â€” advanced Turbo stack (mostly tied to âšˇ speculative).
# (1) Dynamic draft length: when speculative decoding is ON (a draft model is
# used), genesi-ai-turbo adds a draft-length floor + acceptance-probability
# threshold so llama.cpp adapts how many tokens it drafts to the live acceptance
# rate (each flag gated on --help, names vary by version; env GENESI_TURBO_DRAFT
# _MAX/MIN/P). (2) Persistent prompt/KV cache to disk: --slot-save-path (per-user
# cache dir, gated, GENESI_TURBO_NO_SLOT_CACHE=1 to disable) enables llama-server
# slot save/restore. (3) Advisor â†’ Turbo model pick: `genesi-ai-turbo recommend`
# prints the biggest model that fits 100% in VRAM; the Monitor shows it as a
# one-click "Recomendado p/ sua GPU" chip. (4) Monitor now makes EXPLICIT that
# the âšˇ toggle enables speculative decoding + dynamic draft + persistent KV
# (card text + tooltips). Spec stays OFF by default (still đź”´ BLOCKED on Vulkan/
# NVK); these wins need validation on a real CUDA install via `bench`.
# 2026-06-08 (66): more roadmap items. (1) 2.8.7 sched-ext: opt-in advanced.conf
# `sched_ext = on|<scheduler>[:mode]` loads a BPF sched_ext scheduler in "server"
# (throughput) mode via scxctl on the aggressive path and switches back to what
# ran before on disable; capability-gated on a sched_ext kernel + scxctl (CachyOS
# scx-scheds), silent no-op otherwise. (2) 2.8.3 pre-cache the most-recently-used
# models (plural): the predictive-preload MRU now warms several recent models'
# weight files newest-first while the total stays under ~40% of free RAM. (3) Doc
# only: marked 2.2 (partial offload via -ngl auto, mlock via GENESI_TURBO_MLOCK,
# compositor trim via genesi-ai-kwin-helper) and 2.3 (explicit huge pages on
# demand via advanced.conf) as already-done; rewrote the 2.8.10 speculative-
# decoding item from BLOCKED to a user-toggleable option (no longer a blocker).
# 2026-06-08 (67): Monitor backend install now offers CUDA vs Vulkan with a
# hardware-based recommendation. Clicking "Instalar Backend" opens a dialog that
# explains both and recommends one: CUDA when nvidia-smi works (NVIDIA + the
# proprietary/open driver loaded, ~1.5â€“2Ă— faster), Vulkan otherwise (universal,
# the shipped genesi-llama-cpp, runs on any GPU incl. nouveau/NVK). Vulkan
# installs genesi-llama-cpp via pkexec; CUDA builds llama.cpp-cuda via the user's
# AUR helper (paru/yay) â€” best-effort, with clear warnings when nvidia-smi is
# down or no AUR helper exists. New backend: backendInfo()/backendAdvice signal +
# installTurboBackend(kind). Our backend stays Vulkan by default.
# 2026-06-08 (68): real-world live-ISO fixes. (1) Widget "Abrir AI Mode Monitor"
# did nothing: the plasmoid launched it via the executable engine, which kills
# the child when the popup closes (and PATH wasn't guaranteed). Now launches
# detached with an absolute path (`setsid -f /usr/local/bin/genesi-ai-monitor`).
# (2) Monitor "baixar modelo"/chat/loadModels failed with "Errno 111 Connection
# refused" when ollama was installed but its service wasn't running. The Monitor
# now auto-starts ollama (systemctl start, then a user `ollama serve` fallback)
# before talking to the API, with a clear message if it still can't.
# 2026-06-08 (69): standardize ALL user-facing strings to English (the project
# default). Translated the AI Mode Monitor UI (Main.qml, ChatPage.qml,
# AdvisorPage.qml, ChatBubble.qml) + every backend status/error message in
# genesi_ai_monitor.py, the plasmoid widget strings, and genesi-ai-turbo's
# `serve` terminal output. No behavior change â€” text only.
# 2026-06-09 (70): 2.6 follow-up â€” SMART auto-detect (no more "latched ON
# forever"). genesi-aid drove AI Mode off `bool(ai_processes)`, but `ollama
# serve` is a persistent daemon â†’ the process is ALWAYS present â†’ AI Mode never
# powered back down and the box sat in performance/locked-GPU-clocks at idle.
# Now it classifies the live workload: active (GPU/CPU crunching, or a one-shot
# CLI) â†’ full "max"; warm (a model is resident via ollama keep_alive / a Turbo
# server, but idle) â†’ eases to "balanced" (governor stays, GPU clock/power locks
# released); idle (server listening, nothing loaded) â†’ powers down. Hysteresis
# prevents flapping between chat turns: instant promote on activity, a 30s hold
# before maxâ†’balanced, and an `ai_idle_timeout` (advanced.conf, default 90s)
# grace before standing down. New state.json field `activity`; the Monitor shows
# generating / warmÂ·idle / standing-by under the AI Mode status. Forced ON/OFF
# and explicit profiles still win. Pure detection change â€” all the optimization
# and reversible-restore machinery is untouched.
# pkgrel 71: reliable Turbo on/off. `free_turbo_port` (CLI) and the Monitor's
# `_stop_turbo` now SIGTERM the llama-server, WAIT for the socket to actually
# release (polling /health / the port), then escalate to SIGKILL â€” so toggling
# Turbo off then on no longer hits "already running" with a stuck server. The
# Monitor also kills a stray Turbo it didn't start (e.g. one launched from a
# terminal), which our tracked-PID-only stop used to leave running.
# pkgrel 72: the Monitor now ASKS which model to run Turbo on. Flipping the
# Turbo switch on opens a model picker (installed models, the GPU-fit pick
# pre-selected) instead of silently starting on whatever Ollama happened to
# have loaded. The chosen model is locked, so the live activeModel poll can no
# longer overwrite it mid-session (the "Turbo started with a model I didn't
# pick" bug). Turning Turbo off releases the lock.
pkgrel=72
pkgdesc='Genesi OS AI Mode - adaptive, reversible local-AI optimizer (CPU/GPU/power) + Plasma 6 widget + monitor app'
arch=('any')
url='https://github.com/zFreshy/GenesiOS'
license=('GPL-3.0-or-later')
# pyside6 + qqc2-desktop-style are pulled in as hard deps so the AI Mode Monitor
# (genesi-ai-monitor) works out of the box, dark-themed, wherever genesi-ai-mode
# is installed â€” the live ISO and the target both list genesi-ai-mode, so pacman
# resolves these automatically (no need to edit package lists / the Calamares
# submodule). kirigami comes transitively via plasma-workspace.
# genesi-llama-cpp (Vulkan llama.cpp, provides=llama.cpp) ships `llama-server`,
# the backend of Genesi Turbo's âšˇ switch. It is shipped by default via the
# install lists (archiso packages_desktop.x86_64 + the Calamares netinstall
# "Genesi OS" group), NOT as a hard dep here: it's built by the SAME publish
# pipeline, so a `depends=genesi-llama-cpp` would make the build-deps step
# `pacman -S` a package that isn't in any repo yet (and makepkg's dep check
# would also fail) â†’ aborting the whole publish. It's an optdepend for docs.
# It conflicts with the AUR llama.cpp variants, so those are no longer listed.
depends=('python' 'python-psutil' 'plasma-workspace' 'pyside6' 'qqc2-desktop-style')
optdepends=(
    'power-profiles-daemon: switch to the performance power profile while AI runs'
    'nvidia-utils: NVIDIA GPU performance mode (persistence + max power limit)'
    'ollama: run local models (genesi-ai-mode bench)'
    'qt6-tools: qdbus for the KWin desktop-effect trimmer'
    'genesi-llama-cpp: Genesi Turbo speculative decoding (llama-server, Vulkan â€” shipped by default)'
)
install="$pkgname.install"
# Opt-in advanced tweaks config (all OFF by default). backup() so pacman writes
# .pacnew instead of clobbering a user's edits on upgrade.
backup=('etc/genesi-ai-mode/advanced.conf')
source=()
sha256sums=()

package() {
    # Daemon + user-facing control CLI
    install -Dm755 "${startdir}/genesi-aid"      "$pkgdir/usr/local/bin/genesi-aid"
    install -Dm755 "${startdir}/genesi-ai-mode"  "$pkgdir/usr/local/bin/genesi-ai-mode"
    install -Dm755 "${startdir}/genesi-ai-turbo"  "$pkgdir/usr/local/bin/genesi-ai-turbo"

    # systemd service
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/genesi-aid.service" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/lib/systemd/system/genesi-aid.service"

    # Runtime dir for user<->daemon IPC (world-writable, on tmpfs)
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/genesi-ai-mode.tmpfiles.conf" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/lib/tmpfiles.d/genesi-ai-mode.conf"

    # Static sysctl tuning
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/99-genesi-ai.conf" \
        "$pkgdir/etc/sysctl.d/99-genesi-ai.conf"

    # Advanced opt-in tweaks (2.8.9) â€” shipped all-OFF + documented (see backup())
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/advanced.conf" \
        "$pkgdir/etc/genesi-ai-mode/advanced.conf"

    # Ollama defaults (only applies once Ollama is installed)
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/genesi-ollama.conf" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/lib/systemd/system/ollama.service.d/10-genesi.conf"

    # pacman hook: auto-enable + start ollama.service when ollama is installed
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/genesi-ollama-enable.hook" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/libalpm/hooks/zz-genesi-ollama-enable.hook"

    # Plasma 6 widget (live dashboard + on/auto/off). Not auto-added to the
    # panel â€” the org.kde.plasma.icon launcher in the default layout already
    # provides the toggle UX; this is here for users who want the status view.
    install -dm755 "$pkgdir/usr/share/plasma/plasmoids/org.genesi.aimode"
    cp -r "${startdir}/plasmoid-aimode/"* \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/plasma/plasmoids/org.genesi.aimode/"

    # AI Mode Monitor â€” standalone Qt6/Kirigami dashboard app
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/genesi_ai_monitor.py" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/genesi_ai_monitor.py"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/Main.qml" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/Main.qml"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/ChatPage.qml" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/ChatPage.qml"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/AdvisorPage.qml" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/AdvisorPage.qml"
    # Shared UI building blocks (brand palette + reusable visual components)
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/Theme.qml" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/Theme.qml"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/GlassCard.qml" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/GlassCard.qml"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/GaugeArc.qml" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/GaugeArc.qml"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/ChatBubble.qml" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/genesi-ai-mode/monitor/ChatBubble.qml"
    install -Dm755 "${startdir}/monitor/genesi-ai-monitor" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/local/bin/genesi-ai-monitor"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/monitor/org.genesi.aimonitor.desktop" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/share/applications/org.genesi.aimonitor.desktop"

    # KWin desktop-effect trimmer (user session) + KDE autostart entry
    install -Dm755 "${startdir}/genesi-ai-kwin-helper" \
        "$pkgdir/usr/local/bin/genesi-ai-kwin-helper"
    install -Dm644 "${startdir}/genesi-ai-kwin-helper.desktop" \
        "$pkgdir/etc/xdg/autostart/genesi-ai-kwin-helper.desktop"
}
